.TH DBX-SMITH-LIST 1 "May 2026" "DbxSmith" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
dbx-smith-list \- Inventory explorer for DbxSmith containers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx-smith-list
[options]
.br

.B --help/-h:
show this help message
.br

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dbx-smith-list
is the inventory explorer for the DbxSmith productivity suite. It displays a unified, color-coded table of all Distrobox containers along with their DbxSmith-specific strategies, image sources, current statuses, and creation dates. This provides a more informative overview than the standard 'distrobox list' command by integrating metadata from the DbxSmith registry.

.SH OUTPUT COLUMNS
.B NAME
The unique identifier for the Distrobox container.
.br
.B STRATEGY
The isolation or identity strategy used during the creation of the container (e.g., standard, ghost, airgapped).
.br
.B IMAGE
The base container image name, truncated if necessary.
.br
.B STATUS
The current execution status of the container (e.g., Up, Exited).
.br
.B CREATED
The date when the container was provisioned using DbxSmith.

.SH EXAMPLES
List all containers:
.br

	dbx-smith-list
.br

Show help:
.br

	dbx-smith-list --help
.br

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
.br
.B CONFIG_DIR
.br
.SH SEE ALSO
dbx-smith(1), dbx-smith-spin(1), dbx-smith-rm(1)
